# --- memvault policy (append to ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md) -----------------------------------
## Storage policy — 3 tiers (enforced)

Where you (Claude) MUST write, by nature of the file — respect on EVERY write:

- **Tier 1 — `~/dev/` = CODE, git ONLY.** A hierarchy whose LEAVES are all **private, pushed**
  git repos (sub-containers grouping related repos are fine). NEVER put non-git content at any
  level. Backup = push to the remote.
- **Tier 2 — `<VAULT_DIR>` = everything durable non-code** you produce (notes, exports, working
  files). It is a cloud-synced folder → replicated off-machine automatically. Write durable
  non-code HERE, never at `~` or inside `~/dev`. Its structure **mirrors `~/dev`'s groups**
  (a music note → `<VAULT_DIR>/music/`), so files are organized like the repos; both sides
  evolve in parallel (the `SessionStart` hook keeps the mirror in step).
- **Tier 3 — `~/.claude/` = disposable/regenerable.** Memories + this `CLAUDE.md` live here
  (Claude Code reads them here) and stay LOCAL, but are backed up to the vault automatically:
  a `Stop` hook copies them after every response, a `SessionStart` hook catches up + relocates
  any stray non-git out of `~/dev`.

A launchd **watchdog** flags (between sessions) any repo not committed/pushed or any non-git
file in `~/dev`. It cannot write the cloud (macOS TCC blocks background jobs); the hooks do,
because they run inside Claude Code (which has Full Disk Access).
# --- end memvault policy ---------------------------------------------------------------
